We just put up a HyperNEAT Users Page:

http://eplex.cs.ucf.edu/hyperNEATpa=
ge/HyperNEAT.html

We have several reasons for making this page available, =
some of which may be of interest to those in this group.  One reason is to =
promote the work of those outside our own EPlex research group.  There is n=
ow a fair amount of significant work on HyperNEAT from outside EPlex and it=
 is difficult for someone interested in HyperNEAT to find out about it from=
 our own publications pages, which only features our own work.  Therefore, =
the HyperNEAT Users Page has a section called, "HyperNEAT Projects and Publ=
ications from Outside EPlex," which features this outside work.

If you wou=
ld like your work featured on this page please let me know and we will be h=
appy to link it.  It does not have to be an official publication.  Software=
, experiments, or informal documents are also welcome.

Another reason for =
the page is to have everything about HyperNEAT available in one place.  Bef=
ore this page, there was no clear destination for people searching for "hyp=
erneat" in search engines.  This page will help people find what they are l=
ooking for in an organized manner.

Finally, we hope the page makes it easi=
er for newcomers to get started.  It has a brief introduction explaining th=
e main concepts at a high level and some pictures that give the gist of the=
 approach without having to read a whole research article.  

Comments are =
welcome,

ken
